Award-winning rapper Olamide aka Baddo Sneh has gifted a N2.4 million wristwatch to a fan who sang his song word-for-word on stage. Baddo recently performed during the Goldberg Takeover party at Lagos Ikeja City mall. While performing, Olamide brought up a fan on stage who he noticed sang one of his songs word-for-word.   Flavour consoles white lady scammed by impersonator     Comedienne Princess reacts to Baba Ijesha’s sentence     VIDEO: Actress Destiny Etiko curses troll tying her…   Olamide promised to sign up the fan if he impressed him after the fan begged for a chance to perform on stage. Appreciating the fan, Olamide removed his N2.4million wristwatch and gave to him. Hayjay went hysterical with Baddo’s gesture as he continued to scream in excitement. He kept saying: “Baddo just gave me his wristwatch! Baddo for life!!”